@startuml fig-http-methods-idempotency
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
left to right direction

title HTTP Methods — Safety, Idempotency and Cacheability

card "**GET**\nRetrieve a resource\n\nSafe: Yes\nIdempotent: Yes\nCacheable: Yes" as GET #C8E6C9

card "**POST**\nCreate / submit\n\nSafe: No\nIdempotent: No\nCacheable: No" as POST #FFCDD2

card "**PUT**\nFull replacement\n\nSafe: No\nIdempotent: Yes\nCacheable: No" as PUT #BBDEFB

card "**PATCH**\nPartial update\n\nSafe: No\nIdempotent: No*\nCacheable: No" as PATCH #FFF9C4

card "**DELETE**\nRemove a resource\n\nSafe: No\nIdempotent: Yes\nCacheable: No" as DELETE #FFE0B2

card "**OPTIONS**\nCapabilities query\n\nSafe: Yes\nIdempotent: Yes\nCacheable: No" as OPTIONS #ECEFF1

GET -[hidden]right-> POST
POST -[hidden]right-> PUT
PUT -[hidden]right-> PATCH
PATCH -[hidden]right-> DELETE
DELETE -[hidden]right-> OPTIONS

legend bottom
  Safe: no side effects on the server.
  Idempotent: repeated calls produce the same result.
  *PATCH is not guaranteed idempotent by specification.
  Proxies and load balancers may retry idempotent methods automatically.
endlegend
@enduml
